cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with image aesthetic assessment, which is a computer vision task, hence cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes a neural network architecture, which involves training and optimization, making cs.AI and cs.LG also likely sub-categories. The paper also involves experiments on datasets, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
